Erin Fredericks (15) was last seen on 2 June at Grassy Park Station. CAPE TOWN - A police and community search for a missing Grassy Park teenager entered its 17th day on Monday.Erin Fredericks, aged 15, was last seen on 2 June at Grassy Park Station.She was wearing a grey jacket and blue jeans at the time of her disappearance.Meanwhile, the Mitchells Plain Crisis Forum's Joanie Fredericks said she was contacted by the teen's distraught mother who pleaded for help to find her child.Fredericks said they will not give up searching for the teenager. We didn t manage to find Erin, but we remain positive we ll find her soon. We ve got a bit of information and we re positive about the leads we have. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)